  "prompt": "How much money is considered to be \"fuck you\" money?",
  "response": "The definition of \"f*** you\" money varies depending on individual perspectives and lifestyle, but generally it refers to having enough financial resources to:\n\n1. Quit your job without immediate financial worry\n2. Walk away from unfavorable work or personal situations\n3. Maintain your current standard of living without needing to work\n\nRough estimates often range from:\n- $1-2 million for more modest lifestyles\n- $5-10 million for upper-middle-class comfort\n- $10-20 million for significant financial freedom\n\nKey factors determining the amount include:\n- Your current living expenses\n- Location/cost of living\n- Desired lifestyle\n- Age and expected years of potential earnings\n- Investment returns\n- Personal risk tolerance\n\nThe core idea is having enough money that you can say \"no\" to things that don't align with your values or make you unhappy, without fear of financial ruin.\n\nFor most people, this isn't about extreme wealth, but about having a meaningful financial cushion that provides genuine personal autonomy and peace of mind.",
